title: Japan to reopen to mass tourism in October
description: Japan, one of the world's last major holdouts during the pandemic, is dissolving its Covid-19 restrictions and opening the door back up to mass tourism.

title: ISIS attempts suicide attack on al-Hol camp in Syria
description: A group of ISIS militants in two vehicles rigged with suicide explosives attempted to attack the al-Hol camp in Syria which holds around 60,000 displaced persons, according to US Central Command.

title: Why Jamie Dimon apologized to Elizabeth Warren
description: JPMorgan CEO Jamie Dimon is testifying on Capitol Hill Thursday for the second straight day. This time, he'll face longtime critic, Sen. Elizabeth Warren.

title: Why it's getting even harder to rent or buy a home
description: Americans looking to buy or rent a home have had a rough year.

title: Mortgage rates rise to nearly 6.3%, the highest since 2008
description: Mortgage rates jumped higher for the fifth week in a row, further pushing past 6% in the face of yet another aggressive rate hike from the Federal Reserve.

title: One-year-old dies as 11 more suspected Ebola cases identified in Uganda
description: Uganda's Ministry of Health reported another 11 suspected cases of Ebola identified in the country's Mubende district as of Tuesday. Of these, the ministry recorded one probable Ebola-related death, a one-year-old, it said in a statement released Tuesday night.

title: Nigeria's Buhari, in last UN speech, slams 'corrosive impact' of leaders who cling to power
description: Nigeria's President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday criticized fellow leaders who extend term limits to cling to power, saying this was having a "corrosive" effect, and promised free and fair elections when the country elects his successor in February.

title: Opinion: The political charmer who repacked Italy's far-right
description: I am often asked what Giorgia Meloni -- leader of the national conservative Brothers of Italy party, and likely next prime minister of the country -- is really up to.

title: Kia, Hyundai are easy targets for thieves, insurance data confirms
description: Stealing older model Hyundai and Kia cars and SUVs became a scary social media trend. Now, data from the Highway Loss Data Institute, which collects information on insurance claims, confirm these South Korean models are far more likely to get stolen than others.

title: 200 whales dead, 35 remain alive after mass stranding in Australia
description: Around 200 whales have died and just 35 remain alive following a mass stranding in Australia this week, rescue teams say.
